JOHANNESBURG – The sugar industry is expected to protest over imports flooding the country. The South African Sugar Association says imports have increased drastically since 2015. READ: SA moves one step closer to a sugar tax, and a healthier lifestyle “Over the past 3 years since 2015, we had 51,000 tons of imports. In 2017 (imports) escalated to 514,000 tons. This is impacting badly on small-scale growers and milling companies,” said South African Sugar Association chairperson Suresh Naidoo. eNCA